### Mongoose ODM

Mongoose is an Object Data Modeling (ODM) library for MongoDB and Node.js.

```bash
npm install mongoose
```

### Schema Definition

Define the structure of documents:

```javascript
const mongoose = require('mongoose');

const userSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  name: { type: String, required: true },
  email: { type: String, required: true, unique: true },
  age: { type: Number, min: 0 },
  createdAt: { type: Date, default: Date.now }
});
```

### Model

Create a Model from a Schema:

```javascript
const User = mongoose.model('User', userSchema);
```

### CRUD with Mongoose

```javascript
// Create
const user = await User.create({ name: 'John', email: 'john@test.com' });

// Find all
const users = await User.find();

// Find by ID
const user = await User.findById('507f1f77bcf86cd799439011');

// Update
const updated = await User.findByIdAndUpdate(id, { name: 'Jane' }, { new: true });

// Delete
await User.findByIdAndDelete(id);
```

### Population (Joins)

Reference documents from other collections:

```javascript
const postSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  title: String,
  author: { type: mongoose.Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'User' }
});

// Populate author
const posts = await Post.find().populate('author');
```

### Validation in Schema

Built-in and custom validators:

```javascript
const schema = new mongoose.Schema({
  email: {
    type: String,
    validate: {
      validator: v => /\S+@\S+\.\S+/.test(v),
      message: props => `${props.value} is not a valid email`
    }
  }
});
```

